**Event Title:** SAINTCON Family Night

**Description:** 
The SAINTCON Family Night Event offers an opportunity for conference attendees to bring their families and showcase the exciting aspects of the conference. It includes various engaging activities focused on critical thinking, creativity, and imagination.

**Event Details:**
- **Date:** October 24, 2024
- **Time:** 6:00 PM - 8:30 PM
- **Target Audience:** Family members of SAINTCON attendees, specifically ages 4-16, but open to all family members.
- **Registration Start Date:** August 17, 2024
- **Cost:** $12 per participant (ages 4-16); accompanying adults do not need to register or pay but can purchase a Family Night T-shirt.
- **Participant Capacity:** Limited to 500 participants, so early registration is advised.

**Activities Include:**
- Kid Talks
- Capture the Flag (CTF) (bring a device)
- Cipher Challenge
- Bristle Bots
- Circuit Building
- Rocket Building
- Soldering Station
- Fingerprint Lifting
- Keyboard Art
- Scavenger Hunt
- Tinfoil Hats
- Lockpicking

**Additional Information:**
- Presentations by kids on STEM topics are encouraged.
- Registration is required for participants; includes an event bag with various supplies.
- Call for artwork submissions for event materials.
- Volunteers are needed to help run events.

